<div class="min-h-screen px-6 sm:px-20 py-12 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
  <h1 class="font-bold text-4xl text-center mb-2">Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
  <p class="text-center text-base-content/60 mb-12">Last updated: March 2026</p>

  <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">1. Assumption of Risk</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
          By using DayTrip, you acknowledge and agree that ridesharing involves inherent risks, including but not
          limited to personal injury, property damage, and accidents. You voluntarily assume all such risks associated
          with any ride arranged through this platform.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">2. No Liability</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
          DayTrip is a platform that connects drivers and passengers. We are not a transportation company and do not
          provide transportation services. DayTrip is not responsible for, and expressly disclaims all liability for,
          any damages, injuries, losses, or claims arising out of or related to any ride arranged through this platform,
          including but not limited to accidents, personal injury, death, or property damage.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">3. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
          DayTrip makes no representations or warranties about the safety, reliability, or suitability of any driver
          or vehicle listed on the platform. We do not verify driving records, insurance coverage, vehicle condition,
          or any other driver qualifications. You use the platform entirely at your own risk.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">4. User Responsibility</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
          Drivers are solely responsible for maintaining valid licenses, appropriate vehicle insurance, and compliance
          with all applicable traffic laws. Passengers are responsible for exercising their own judgment about whether
          to accept a ride. Both parties agree to treat each other with respect and to comply with all applicable laws.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">5. Indemnification</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
          You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless DayTrip, its owners, and affiliates from and against any
          and all claims, damages, losses, costs, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising out of your
          use of the platform or your violation of these Terms.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">6. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
          DayTrip reserves the right to update these Terms at any time. Continued use of the platform after changes
          are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-primary text-primary-content shadow-md">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">Questions?</h2>
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed">
          If you have any questions about these Terms, reach out at any time.
        </p>
        <div class="card-actions mt-4">
          <a href="mailto:support@daytrip.live" class="btn btn-outline btn-sm text-primary-content border-primary-content hover:bg-primary-content hover:text-primary">
            <%= lucide_icon('mail', class: 'w-4 h-4') %>
            Contact Support
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
